    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix TLV padding handling in NFAPI unpacking functions\n\n### Summary\nThe NFAPI library in the OAI5G codebase has incorrect TLV (Type-Length-Value) padding handling in the non-NR versions of TLV unpacking functions. When processing messages with padded TLVs (as required by SCF specification section 2.3.2.1), the unpacking functions fail to advance the read pointer by the correct amount, causing subsequent data to be read incorrectly.\n\nThis specifically affects the `unpack_ul_node_sync` function which calls `unpack_p7_tlv_list` to handle vendor extensions. When these extensions contain padded TLVs, the function reads incorrect data leading to potential crashes or incorrect behavior.\n\nThe root cause was that `unpack_tlv_list` and `unpack_p7_tlv_list` were missing the padding handling that was already correctly implemented in their NR counterparts (`unpack_nr_tlv_list` and `unpack_nr_p7_tlv_list`).\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/nfapi/src/nfapi.c`: \n  - Added padding handling in `unpack_tlv_list` function after processing known TLVs and when skipping unknown TLVs\n  - Added padding handling in `unpack_p7_tlv_list` function after processing known TLVs and when skipping unknown TLVs\n\n"
}